    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You could have a <a href=\"https://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/Map.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Map</a> of <code>type A</code> objects to a <a href=\"https://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/List.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">List</a> or <a href=\"https://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/Set.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Set</a> (or whichever <a href=\"https://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/Collection.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Collection</a> works best) of <code>type B</code> objects, like:</p>\n<pre><code> Map&lt;A,List&lt;B&gt;&gt; map = new HashMap&lt;A,List&lt;B&gt;&gt;();\n</code></pre>\n<p>Or use Google's <a href=\"https://guava.dev/releases/23.0/api/docs/com/google/common/collect/Multimap.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Multimap</a> interface, which will do essentially the same as above, but with less work on your part.</p>\n"
  } ],
